Most people don’t realize there’s an entire industry built around collecting and selling your personal data.<br/>
<br/>
Data brokers compile things like your name, address history, phone number, and even relatives, then sell that data to people-search sites. Once your profile exists, it gets copied, repackaged, and resold across the internet.<br/>
<br/>
That creates two problems<br/>
• Social engineering because bad actors can sound more credible<br/>
• Exposure because strangers can easily look you up online<br/>
<br/>
Even if you remove yourself from one site, your info can come back when brokers republish new data.<br/>
<br/>
That’s why I’ve been a paying DeleteMe customer for the past 1.5+ years, and after using it extensively myself I decided to partner with them.<br/>
