      <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/DFHDYwBNw_x/"><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.75761-15/474493823_17880117372231491_456879018218851626_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_s640x640_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=108&amp;ig_cache_key=MzU1MDgyMTcyNjE3MTg5Mzc0NTE3ODgwMTE3MzY2MjMxNDkx.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjEwODB4MTkyMC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=8lJxwxyj20kQ7kNvwEOaQV4&amp;_nc_oc=Adq1XebvTCQ02PanFSJRKTLJU8VdKZ5hgPUBngLhjkyvi3BzquKCV0K8Kju1K96VXd0&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=tecc0j53IJsKiTX7Qr02TQ&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afxf5wChbW2VveKIuxof4ckAtXIPE0StSR8I_FHWyJu3nQ&amp;oe=69CA17CE" alt="Video-thumbnail fra @addielamarr.sh" /></a></p><p><strong>🎬 Video</strong></p><p><strong>@addielamarr.sh</strong></p><p>We need to have a serious conversation right now—especially for marginalized communities. With new laws and policies targeting personal freedoms, your text messages could get you into real trouble. <br/>
<br/>
Why? <br/>
<br/>
Because text messages aren’t sent directly from phone to phone. Instead, they pass through a Short Message Service Center (SMSC), where they’re stored, scanned, and left vulnerable to surveillance. <br/>
<br/>
If you’re seeking healthcare, have a friend who is undocumented, are part of the queer community, or involved in any kind of resistance, your messages could be used against you. <br/>
<br/>
The solution? Stop using your phone’s native texting app immediately. Switch to apps like Signal or Threema (for all messages, not just sensitive ones), which offer end-to-end encryption to keep your conversations private. Your safety and privacy are worth the change.<br/>
<br/>
